cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning in computational modeling of sensory information processing, which is a topic that falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper focuses on deep neural networks and their use in modeling sensory information processing. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper discusses the use of machine learning methods in neuroimaging to test computational models of sensory information processing. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses model comparison techniques and their use in evaluating deep neural networks. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses the goal of understanding intelligence and simulating perception and behavior in computational systems. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper briefly mentions the use of new model comparison techniques that allow for stronger conclusions to be made about the computational mechanisms underlying sensory information processing.
